1. Generate FlipGC background sequence
	cmdprompt: perl FlipGC_sequence.pl ChromosomeZ.fa StartNumber NumberOfFilesToGenerate
	example: perl FlipGC_sequence.pl ChromosomeZ.fa 1 1000
		generate 1000 files contained FlipGC sequence of the specified chromosome
	example: perl FlipGC_sequence.pl ChromosomeZ.fa 200 100
		generate 100 files starting at number 200: ChromosomeZ_200.fa ChromosomeZ_201.fa ... ChromosomeZ_300.fa
		allows user to run smaller batches of files

2. Identify motif library within sequence files. 
	#Requires MotifLibrary.txt to contain motifs of same length on separate lines
	
	MotifLibrary.txt:
	GACCACCCA 1
	TGGGTGGTC 1
	...

	A. Identity motifs within the native chromosome file 
		cmdprompt: perl IdentifyMotifs.pl ChromosomeZ.fa MotifLibrary.txt
	   		generates a file (named from the input files- Coords_MotifLibrary_ChromsomeZ.txt) containing the start locations, types of motifs, and motif score found in the ChromosomeZ.fa file
	
	B. Identify motifs across all of the FlipGC sequence files generated from the native chromosome
		background sequence used to generate the background chromosomes can be moved to a separate directory and run in a batch
		move to new subdirectory
			cmdprompt: for file in *.fa; do perl ../IdentifyMotifs.pl $file ../Motifs.txt; done
		
		concatenate all of the Coords files into one Batch file for the next step
			cat Coords_Motif_chr_* > Batch_MotifLibrary_BackgroundSequenceChromsomeZ.txt
	
3. Build background chromosomes containing the same number and types of motifs found in the native chromosome.
	Returns one file which contains the coordinates for all the background chromosomes.
	#Requires Coords_MotifLibrary_ChromosomeZ.txt and Batch_MotifLibrary_BackgroundSequenceChromosomeZ.txt as input
	
	cmdprompt: perl BuildBackgroundChromosomes.pl Coords_MotifLibrary_ChromosomeZ.txt Batch_MotifLibrary_BackgroundSequenceChromsomeZ.txt NumberOfBakgroundChromosomes
	example: perl BuildBackgroundChromosomes.pl Coords_Gli_ChromosomeZ.txt Batch_Gli_BackgroundSequenceChromosomeZ.txt 100
		#generates a file named Coords_Gli_ChromsomeZ_BGchr_100.txt containing back to back chromosomes with the same composition as the native chromosome
		
4. Calculate the cluster coefficient
	#Requires a sorted file generated by BuildBackgroundChromosomes.pl script
	use either Unix sort command or excel to sort the file in ascending order
	cmdprompt: sort Coords_Gli_ChromsomeZ_BGchr_100.txt > S_Coords_Gli_ChromsomeZ_BGchr_100.txt
	
	cmdprompt: perl CalculateClusterCoefficient.pl Coords_Gli_ChromosomeZ.txt S_Coords_Gli_ChromsomeZ_BGchr_100.txt Clustersize MaximumClusterLength
		Generates cluster coefficients for clusters of specified size.
		Output file format: chromosome	motif start	motif end	motif	predicted motif affinity	cluster start coord	cluster end coord	average cluster predicted affinity	cluster coefficient
